text.tspan: \fRomanS|b0|i0;The size of a fillet weld is always referred to the thickness of the throat. Not-indicated weldings will be 0.4 x minimum thickness of the plate (when it is welded on both sides) and 0.7 x minimum thickness (when it is just one side welded)
